🎮 Rock Paper Scissors – Python

A simple command-line Rock, Paper, Scissors game built in Python as part of my Python learning journey. 🐍
The game allows the user to play multiple rounds against the computer, keeps track of the score, and includes input validation to prevent invalid entries.

✨ Features

🎲 Play Rock, Paper, Scissors against the computer
🖼️ ASCII art display for each move
🔀 Random computer choices using Python's random module
🔁 Continuous gameplay until the player chooses to stop
📊 Score tracking for both player and computer
🛡️ Input validation for:
Player move selection
Replay choice (Y/N)
👤 Personalized gameplay using the player's name

🧠 Concepts Practiced:

This project helped reinforce several core Python concepts:
📋 Lists
🔀 Conditional statements (if, elif, else)
🔁 while loops
🧩 Nested loops
✅ Input validation
🎲 The random module
🎮 Basic game logic
📈 Variables and score tracking

Example Gameplay
What do you choose Ahmed? Type 0 for rock, 1 for paper, 2 for scissors

0
Computer Chose:
1

You lose!

Current Scorecard: Ahmed : 0, Computer : 1

